-- 
Mol, CEZ Start Joint Power-Plant Project, Vilaggazdasag Reports

-- B y   E d i t h   B a l a z s
-- 
2011-09-09T05:48:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-09/mol-cez-start-joint-power-plant-project-vilaggazdasag-reports.html
Mol Nyrt.,  Hungary ’s biggest oil
company, and  CEZ AS (CEZ) , the Czech Republic’s largest utility, have
started preparations for the construction of a joint power plant
in Hungary,  Vilaggazdasag  reported.  The two companies, which agreed to spend 1.4 billion euros
($1.9 billion) to build two gas-fired power plants in Slovakia
and Hungary, plan to have the Hungarian plant fully operational
by April 30, 2014, the newspaper said.  The power plant will have a capacity of at least 840
megawatts, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Edith Balazs in Budapest at 
 ebalazs1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at 
 jagomez@bloomberg.net  